    People also ask
    Which is the largest hospital in Sri Lanka?
    The National Hospital
    The National Hospital situated in Colombo in a 32 acre block of land is the largest teaching hospital in Sri Lanka and the final referral centre in the country consisting of 3000 beds.

    What is the first hospital in Sri Lanka?
    Ruins of a hospital in Mihintale which was built by King Sena II (851-885 A.C.) that dates back to the 9th century has been discovered and it is considered one of the world's oldest hospitals.

    What is the name of the hospital in Ragama?
    Colombo North Teaching Hospital (CNTH) which is situated at Ragama in the Gampaha District is 18 km away from the capital of Sri Lanka.

    What is the bed capacity of the National Hospital of Sri Lanka?
